## Valuation

This is Meridian's own estimate, not company guidance. We anchor on normalized earnings power, not the trough cycle. FY2025 diluted EPS was $4.83. We assume the freight cycle inflects modestly off two years of historically low routing-guide depth (1.2–1.5, where 1.0 is perfect;

[10-Q](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1043277/000104327726000016/chrw-20260331.htm), and that the margin set holds. On a base-case normalized EPS of roughly $5.75–$6.25 (our number: cycle recovery + retained cost-out, not a filing figure), a 21–23x forward multiple — a premium to a pure cyclical broker, justified if the take-rate proves structural — implies a $125–$140 target. The bear/cyclical framing would cap the multiple at ~15x trough EPS and argues the margin gives back. The gap between those two outcomes is wide enough that getting the take-rate question right is the whole trade.
